# Cablenet HR — MVP Dashboard

An MVP HR admin dashboard for **Cablenet** (Cypriot telecom). Built with
**React + Vite + Tailwind CSS v4**. Visual identity derives from Cablenet's
brand — violet (`#5B2D8E`) primary with an orange accent and a "signal / fibre"
motif throughout.

## Features

- **Overview** — headline KPIs, headcount trend, pending approvals, hiring
  pipeline, onboarding progress and an activity feed.
- **People Directory** — searchable/filterable directory (grid + table views)
  with a detailed profile drawer (contact, role, leave balance, skills).
- **Time Off & Attendance** — leave approval queue (approve/reject), who's out
  today, weekly coverage and utilisation stats.
- **Workforce Analytics** — headcount trajectory, hires vs exits, gender
  balance, tenure distribution and location split (custom SVG charts).
- **Recruiting & Onboarding** — open requisitions, candidate pipeline funnel,
  candidate table and onboarding checklists.
- **CV Screening** — paste or upload a CV, pick a role, and get a transparent
  match score with a per-requirement breakdown, matched/missing skills and
  signals. Runs locally.
- **HR Assistant (RAG)** — ask natural-language questions about your people,
  time off, recruiting and analytics. Answers are retrieved from the
  dashboard's own data and composed with cited sources. Available as a global
  slide-over and a full page.

> The CV screening and HR assistant are **local, deterministic engines** that
> retrieve over the bundled mock data — they do not call an external LLM. This
> keeps the MVP self-contained and offline-capable.

## Getting started

```bash
npm install
npm run dev      # start the dev server
npm run build    # production build
npm run preview  # preview the production build
```

## Tech

- React 18 + React Router
- Tailwind CSS v4 (`@tailwindcss/vite`, CSS-first theme tokens)
- `@fontsource` (Sora / Inter / JetBrains Mono — bundled, no CDN)
- `lucide-react` icons
- Hand-built SVG charts (area, bars, donut, funnel, sparkline)

All data is mock/seeded in `src/data/mockData.js`.

_Deployed via GitHub Actions → Vercel on each push to `main`._

_Live at https://ckontz-gt.github.io/HR-Cablenet-Dashboard/_
